lgpAgentIdentModel.name: lgpAgentIdentModel
lgpAgentIdentModel.description: The agent model designation. This identifier is typically a model name or ID

lgpAgentIdentFirmwareVersion.name: lgpAgentIdentFirmwareVersion
lgpAgentIdentFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware revision level of the agent.

lgpAgentIdentSerialNumber.name: lgpAgentIdentSerialNumber
lgpAgentIdentSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the agent. This is a string of alphanumeric characters that uniquely identifies the agent hardware. This number is assigned when the agent hardware is manufactured and does not change throughout its lifecycle.

lgpAgentIdentPartNumber.name: lgpAgentIdentPartNumber
lgpAgentIdentPartNumber.description: The agent model part number designation.

lgpAgentConnectedDeviceCount.name: lgpAgentConnectedDeviceCount
lgpAgentConnectedDeviceCount.description: The number of devices currently connected and communicating successfully with the agent. Devices for which communications are currently being attempted are not considered in this count.

lgpAgentDeviceCommunicationLost.name: lgpAgentDeviceCommunicationLost
lgpAgentDeviceCommunicationLost.description: The agent has lost communications with a managed device.

lgpAgentFirmwareUpdateSuccessful.name: lgpAgentFirmwareUpdateSuccessful
lgpAgentFirmwareUpdateSuccessful.description: The firmware update to the agent card has completed successfully.

lgpAgentFirmwareCorrupt.name: lgpAgentFirmwareCorrupt
lgpAgentFirmwareCorrupt.description: The firmware update to the agent card has failed and the firmware is now corrupt.

lgpAgentDnsLookupFailure.name: lgpAgentDnsLookupFailure
lgpAgentDnsLookupFailure.description: A Domain Name System (DNS) lookup of a network name failed to resolve. This may result in one or more of the following: 1. failure to notify a target address of an important condition 2. failure allow access for monitoring purposes This issue should be resolved as soon as possible with a network or system administrator.

lgpAgentManagedDeviceTable.name: lgpAgentManagedDeviceTable
lgpAgentManagedDeviceTable.description: This table contains one entry for each managed device.

lgpAgentManagedDeviceEntry.name: lgpAgentManagedDeviceEntry
lgpAgentManagedDeviceEntry.description: This entry describes a row in the table 'lgpAgentManagedDeviceTable'. The rows in this table cannot be created by the NMS. The rows are automatically created by the agent based upon the hardware configuration of the Liebert managed device(s) being monitored with this agent.

lgpAgentDeviceIndex.name: lgpAgentDeviceIndex
lgpAgentDeviceIndex.description: The device identifier. This is used as an index to address a particular row in the table 'lgpAgentManagedDeviceTable'.

lgpAgentDeviceId.name: lgpAgentDeviceId
lgpAgentDeviceId.description: The managed device specific identifier defined by the product registration.

lgpAgentDeviceFirmwareVersion.name: lgpAgentDeviceFirmwareVersion
lgpAgentDeviceFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware revision level of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceUnitNumber.name: lgpAgentDeviceUnitNumber
lgpAgentDeviceUnitNumber.description: The managed device unit number. Typically this is a number assigned to a managed device that uniquely identifies it from other similar devices within a 'system'.

lgpAgentDeviceSerialNumber.name: lgpAgentDeviceSerialNumber
lgpAgentDeviceSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceManufactureDate.name: lgpAgentDeviceManufactureDate
lgpAgentDeviceManufactureDate.description: The manufacture date of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceServiceContact.name: lgpAgentDeviceServiceContact
lgpAgentDeviceServiceContact.description: The service contact of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceServicePhoneNumber.name: lgpAgentDeviceServicePhoneNumber
lgpAgentDeviceServicePhoneNumber.description: The phone number of the service contact of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine1.name: lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine1
lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine1.description: Line 1 of the service address of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine2.name: lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine2
lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine2.description: Line 2 of the service address of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine3.name: lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine3
lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine3.description: Line 3 of the service address of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine4.name: lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine4
lgpAgentDeviceServiceAddrLine4.description: Line 4 of the service address of the managed device.

lgpAgentDeviceUnitName.name: lgpAgentDeviceUnitName
lgpAgentDeviceUnitName.description: Unit name for the managed device assigned by the customer.

lgpAgentDeviceSiteIdentifier.name: lgpAgentDeviceSiteIdentifier
lgpAgentDeviceSiteIdentifier.description: Identifier that uniquely identifies the site where this device is located.

lgpAgentDeviceTagNumber.name: lgpAgentDeviceTagNumber
lgpAgentDeviceTagNumber.description: Identifier that uniquely identifies this device within a particular site (see lgpAgentDeviceSiteIdentifier).

lgpAgentReboot.name: lgpAgentReboot
lgpAgentReboot.description: Perform an immediate 'reboot' of the agent process. When possible the reboot will approximate a power on reset of the agent communications hardware. This type of reboot will be performed if a hardware reset is supported by the hardware/software on the communications card. Otherwise a 'software' reboot will be executed. In both cases a temporary loss of communications and other agent functionality will result. Any valid INTEGER value may be written to this object to initiate the reboot operation. If read the value '0' will always be returned.

lgpAgentTelnetEnabled.name: lgpAgentTelnetEnabled
lgpAgentTelnetEnabled.description: This object represents the settings of Telnet. yes Telnet services are enabled. no Telnet services are disabled. The system must be rebooted before changes can take effect.

lgpAgentVelocityServerEnabled.name: lgpAgentVelocityServerEnabled
lgpAgentVelocityServerEnabled.description: This object configures the Velocity Server to grant external clients access to agent data via the Liebert Velocity protocol. yes Agent data is available to external clients via the Liebert Velocity protocol. no Agent data is not available to external clients via the Liebert Velocity protocol. The system must be rebooted before changes can take effect.

lgpAgentWebServerMode.name: lgpAgentWebServerMode
lgpAgentWebServerMode.description: This object represents the settings of Web services. disabled Web services are disabled. http Web server mode is HTTP (not secure). https Web server mode is secure HTTP. The system must be rebooted before changes can take effect.
